---
description: Persist session changes to the memory bank — run at the end of a session or after significant changes
---

You are updating the Memory Bank to reflect what happened in this session. Follow each step in order.

## Step 1 — Review the session

Reflect on the current conversation and identify:
- What was built, changed, or decided
- Any new patterns, constraints, or architectural decisions discovered
- What is still in progress or blocked
- What the next logical step is

## Step 2 — Determine which files need updating

Only update files where something actually changed. Do not rewrite files that are still accurate.

| File | Update when... |
|---|---|
| `memory-bank/activeContext.md` | Current focus, recent changes, or next steps changed |
| `memory-bank/progress.md` | Work was completed, started, or blocked |
| `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md` | A new architectural pattern or design decision was made |
| `memory-bank/techContext.md` | A new dependency, tool, or constraint was introduced |
| `memory-bank/productContext.md` | The product goals or user experience direction shifted |
| `memory-bank/projectbrief.md` | Core project scope or requirements changed (rare) |

## Step 3 — Update each file

For each file that needs updating:
1. Read the current contents
2. Make the minimal edit that reflects what changed — do not rewrite content that is still accurate
3. Write the updated file

Always update `activeContext.md` and `progress.md` unless the session had no meaningful changes.

## Step 4 — Confirm

After all updates, list each file that was changed and briefly state what was updated. State: "Memory bank updated."
